sum(delta[i])` over all
stations, - `tank =` running
sum from the current candidate
..."];
claim [shape=box style="rounded,filled" fillcolor="#DCFCE7" color="#94A3B8" penwidth=1.2 margin="0.18,0.12" fontname="Helvetica" fontsize=12 label="Deficit Elimination Lemma
Suppose the running sum from
`start` through `i` is
negative. Then no station `k`
with `start <= k <= i` can be
..."];
action [shape=box style="rounded,filled" fillcolor="#FDE68A" color="#94A3B8" penwidth=1.2 margin="0.18,0.12" fontname="Helvetica" fontsize=12 label="Algorithm Consequence
Compute `delta[i] = gas[i] -
cost[i]` on the fly. 2.
Accumulate `total +=
delta[i]`. 3. Accumulate `tank
..."];
proof [shape=box style="rounded,filled" fillcolor="#FCE7F3" color="#94A3B8" penwidth=1.2 margin="0.18,0.12" fontname="Helvetica" fontsize=12 label="Why It Works
If `total < 0`, the total gas
is less than the total cost,
so no complete cycle can
succeed from any start."];
